subSection.paragraph:
Forest lizards of the genus 

Calotes

Cuvier, 1817 represent the third-most diverse 
Draconinae
genus, with a total of 25 currently recognized species (
Pal et al. 2018
; 
Uetz et al. 2023
). Members of the genus are widely distributed throughout Asia, from Sri Lanka across southern Himalaya to Southeast Asia (
Manthey 2010
). While considerable progress has been made on the taxonomy of the genus in the Indian subcontinent (
Deepak et al. 2015
; 
Gowande et al. 2016
, 
2021
; 
Pal et al. 2018
; 
Giri et al. 2019
) and the Indochinese region (
Hallermann 2000
; 
Zug et al. 2006
; 
Vindum et al. 2003
; 
Hartmann et al. 2013
), far less attention has been given to species from the Pan-Himalayan Region, particularly species of the 

C. jerdoni

complex.

